snippet.textDisplay:
The statement that "... you can tune in whenever you like over the weekend! " was not quite true!



Was enjoying watching "Joseph's Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat" with the family but the video stopped abruptly about 2pm Central Daylight Time on Sunday afternoon... which may have been about 7pm GMT. If the video access was granted at 7pm on Friday, then the access was discontinued promptly after 48 hours... even for those in the midst of watching it.



I believe that Andrew Lloyd Weber and TheShowsMustGoOn could have communicated much better to manage expectations.
The misleading statement that "... YOU CAN TUNE IN WHENEVER YOU LIKE OVER THE WEEKEND! " was especially unappreciated due to current lockdown circumstances which limit the number of things for families to look forward to.



Disappointing!

:(

snippet.textDisplay: Oh my word!!  What a treat that was!  Thank you so much Sir Andrew for putting on Joseph.  Its the first thing for weeks to cheer me up and make me smile.  ...  Having first watched Joseph in 1976 as a school production I've seen it countless times since as I always love it.  It was a real joy to see Donny  (who I first fell in love with in the 70's) as Joseph.  But my very favourite Joseph has always been Mike Holoway and his interpretation  of Close Every Door to Me so touched me at the time and has stayed in my memory for all these years.  Thank you. x
